ideo is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/29GUfvdOVJg\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Copy content to copied here.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/bK8RLzjcwfg\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/bK8RLzjcwfg\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Copy content to copied here.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Health Webinar with New York City Department of Health</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/iv61DmRvH7Y\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/iv61DmRvH7Y\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Copy content to copied here.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>What Should You Do If You Feel Sick?</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/1-2vy_SoOqo\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/1-2vy_SoOqo\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/wJ9z-IcIIaQ\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/wJ9z-IcIIaQ\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you have any COVID-19 symptoms, like fever, shortness of breath, and cough, call a doctor immediately. As a Drivers Benefits member, you get free, 24/7 access to MDLIVE*. You and your immediate family can use the app, or call directly, to chat with a doctor in more than 150 languages whenever or wherever.&nbsp;<strong>Click here to download the MDLIVE app on the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/mdlive/id839671393\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Apple App Store&nbsp;</a>or the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.mdlive.mobile&amp;hl=en_US\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Google Play Store</a>&nbsp;today, or just call at&nbsp;<a href=\"tel:888-574-2864\">1-888-574-2864</a>.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>You can use the app to schedule an appointment so you don’t need to wait on the phone or risk going to a crowded doctor’s office.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you’re not yet a member, sign up today&nbsp;<a href=\"https://driversbenefits.org/activate-now/?utm_source=WB&amp;utm_medium=lp&amp;utm_campaign=Covid19\">here</a>&nbsp;or call&nbsp;<a href=\"tel:1-833-814-8590\">1-833-814-8590</a>&nbsp;to activate your benefits today.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>*MDLIVE is paid for by The Black Car Fund.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Get Tested</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The New York City Department of Health and Mental Hygiene is recommending anyone who has COVID-19 symptoms should get a test.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are plenty of ways to find a test near you:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>New York City Department of Health testing website is&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www1.nyc.gov/site/coronavirus/get-tested/covid-19-testing.page\">here.</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>New York State Department of Health testing website is&nbsp;<a href=\"https://coronavirus.health.ny.gov/covid-19-testing\">here.</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can get a free walk-in test at the locations listed&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.nychealthandhospitals.org/covid-19-testing-sites/\">here</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you have questions about any symptoms you’re experiencing and don’t have a primary care provider, you can call the 24-hour state hotline at<a href=\"tel: 1-888-364-3065\">1-888-364-3065</a>,&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href=\"tel: 311\">311&nbsp;</a>to receive assistance on making an appointment for a COVID-19 test.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Sign up for Duke Community Health Watch</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You should also consider signing up for Duke Community Health Watch. In this program, they will:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Help you monitor any symptoms you may be having and provide guidance on how to care for yourself at home</li><li>Provide guidance on when to seek medical care if your symptoms increase</li><li>Support you in following recommendations from the Centers for Disease Control and your local public health department</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you are interested in learning more about the program and applying, please click&nbsp;<a href=\"https://covidwatch.dukehealth.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">here</a>&nbsp;for more information.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Additional Resources</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you still have questions about COVID-19 and driving, we recommend you go to the CDC’s guidance on “Rideshare, Taxi, Limo, and other Passenger Drivers-for-Hire”&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/community/organizations/rideshare-drivers-for-hire.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">here</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Health & Safety','','inherit','closed','closed','','371-revision-v1','','','2020-09-01 18:29:52','2020-09-01 23:29:52','',371,'http://drivers-benefits.local/news/371-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (373,2,'2020-09-01 18:33:25','2020-09-01 23:33:25','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1>Cuidando a los conductores durante COVID-19s</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Drivers Benefits se compromete a proporcionar noticias relevantes para los conductores sobre cómo protegerse y qué hacer si están enfermos. Para proporcionar noticias oportunas, estamos utilizando Google Translate. Vamos a actualizar esta página y continuar haciéndola mejor.<strong>En un esfuerzo por enviarle esta página rápidamente, hemos decidido utilizar Google Translate como nuestro servicio de traducción temporal. Perdónanos si hay algún error.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1>¿Qué es COVID-19?</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>COVID-19, también conocido como Coronavirus, es un virus muy contagioso y peligroso, con síntomas que incluyen dificultad para respirar, fiebre y / o tos.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>¿Quién está en riesgo?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Todos están en riesgo. Pero los que corren un mayor riesgo de enfermarse son los adultos mayores y los que padecen enfermedades cardíacas, diabetes y enfermedades pulmonares.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/index.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Puede obtener más información sobre COVID-19 de los CDC aquí</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>¿Cómo se propaga?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Se cree que el virus se propaga principalmente de persona a persona.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Entre personas que están en contacto cercano entre sí (dentro de unos 6 pies).</li><li>A través de gotas respiratorias producidas cuando una persona infectada tose o estornuda.</li><li>Estas gotitas pueden caer en la boca o la nariz de las personas cercanas o posiblemente ser inhaladas a los pulmones.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>¿Alguien puede transmitir el virus sin estar enfermo?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Se cree que las personas son más contagiosas cuando son más sintomáticas (las más enfermas).</li><li>Es posible que se propague algo antes de que las personas muestren síntomas; Ha habido informes de que esto ocurre con este nuevo coronavirus, pero no se cree que esta sea la principal forma en que se propaga el virus.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Propagación del contacto con superficies u objetos contaminados.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Es posible que una persona pueda contraer COVID-19 al tocar una superficie u objeto que tiene el virus y luego tocarse la boca, la nariz o posiblemente los ojos, pero no se cree que esta sea la forma principal en que el virus untado.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1>¿Cómo mantenerse seguro?</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Como conductor, entra en contacto con muchas personas durante todo el día, lo que aumenta el riesgo de contraer el virus o propagarlo. A continuación se presentan formas de mantenerse seguro y saludable:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Cómo limpiar su auto</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wZ-cyxVUmg8\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wZ-cyxVUmg8\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Desinfecte las partes del automóvil que se tocan con mayor frecuencia: volante, asientos traseros, manijas de pasajeros, cinturones de seguridad, botones del automóvil y reposacabezas.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/2020/03/12/coronavirus-car-interior-cleaning-how-to/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Aquí hay consejos más detallados sobre cómo limpiar su automóvil durante el Coronavirus.</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Cómo lavarse las manos</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-ELZ0bcMfkM\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-ELZ0bcMfkM\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sabemos que es difícil encontrar un baño para lavarse las manos, por lo que recomendamos mantener lo siguiente en su automóvil para que pueda lavarse las manos mientras viaja:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Botella de agua con gorra deportiva</li><li>Jabón</li><li>Toallas de papel para que puedas secarte completamente las manos</li><li>Bolsa de plástico para tirar la toalla de papel</li><li>Recuerde que debe lavarse las manos durante al menos 20 segundos.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bQCP7waTRWU\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Aquí hay un video para mostrarle cómo lavarse las manos adecuadamente, para que no olvide ningún lugar oculto.</a></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>El coronavirus se está extendiendo rápidamente por todo el mundo. La mejor manera de mantenerse a salvo a sí mismo, a su familia y a su comunidad es quedarse en casa si cree que podría enfermarse, incluso si se trata solo del resfriado común. Además, evite el espacio público y manténgase alejado de las personas cuando no esté conduciendo.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://driversbenefits.org/disinfect\">Haga clic aquí para leer sobre más formas de mantenerse a salvo.</a></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1>¿Qué debe hacer si se siente enfermo?</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Cómo obtener acceso gratuito a un médico las 24 horas del día, los 7 días de la semana con \"Drivers Benefits\"</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gLFONWswfnI\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gLFONWswfnI\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Haga una cita.</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yMEZsownD1s\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yMEZsownD1s\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Si tiene algún síntoma de COVID-19, como fiebre, dificultad para respirar y tos, llame a un médico de inmediato. Como miembro de Drivers Benefits, obtienes acceso gratuito las 24 horas, los 7 días de la semana a MDLIVE *. Usted y su familia inmediata pueden usar la aplicación, o llamar directamente, para chatear con un médico en más de 150 idiomas cuando y donde sea.&nbsp;<strong>CHaga clic aquí para descargar la aplicación MDLIVE en&nbsp;<a href=\"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/mdlive/id839671393\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Apple App Store&nbsp;</a>o&nbsp;<a href=\"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.mdlive.mobile&amp;hl=en_US\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Google Play Store</a>&nbsp;hoy mismo, o simplemente llame al&nbsp;<a href=\"tel:888-574-2864\">1-888-574-2864</a>.&nbsp;</strong><strong>Actualmente, los tiempos de espera de MDLIVE son más largos de lo habitual. Sin embargo, están contratando más médicos, por lo que esto no debería seguir siendo un problema. Puede usar la aplicación para programar una cita para no tener que esperar por teléfono o arriesgarse a acudir a un consultorio abarrotado.&nbsp;</strong>Si aún no es miembro, regístrese hoy aquí o llame al&nbsp;<a href=\"tel:1-833-814-8590\">1-833-814-8590</a>&nbsp;para activar sus beneficios hoy.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Health & Safety','','inherit','closed','closed','','371-revision-v1','','','2020-09-01 18:33:25','2020-09-01 23:33:25','',371,'http://drivers-benefits.local/news/371-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (374,2,'2020-09-01 18:34:36','2020-09-01 23:34:36','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Cuidando a los conductores durante COVID-19s</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Drivers Benefits se compromete a proporcionar noticias relevantes para los conductores sobre cómo protegerse y qué hacer si están enfermos. Para proporcionar noticias oportunas, estamos utilizando Google Translate. Vamos a actualizar esta página y continuar haciéndola mejor.<strong>En un esfuerzo por enviarle esta página rápidamente, hemos decidido utilizar Google Translate como nuestro servicio de traducción temporal. Perdónanos si hay algún error.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>¿Qué es COVID-19?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>COVID-19, también conocido como Coronavirus, es un virus muy contagioso y peligroso, con síntomas que incluyen dificultad para respirar, fiebre y / o tos.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>¿Quién está en riesgo?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Todos están en riesgo. Pero los que corren un mayor riesgo de enfermarse son los adultos mayores y los que padecen enfermedades cardíacas, diabetes y enfermedades pulmonares.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/index.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Puede obtener más información sobre COVID-19 de los CDC aquí</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>¿Cómo se propaga?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Se cree que el virus se propaga principalmente de persona a persona.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Entre personas que están en contacto cercano entre sí (dentro de unos 6 pies).</li><li>A través de gotas respiratorias producidas cuando una persona infectada tose o estornuda.</li><li>Estas gotitas pueden caer en la boca o la nariz de las personas cercanas o posiblemente ser inhaladas a los pulmones.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>¿Alguien puede transmitir el virus sin estar enfermo?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Se cree que las personas son más contagiosas cuando son más sintomáticas (las más enfermas).</li><li>Es posible que se propague algo antes de que las personas muestren síntomas; Ha habido informes de que esto ocurre con este nuevo coronavirus, pero no se cree que esta sea la principal forma en que se propaga el virus.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Propagación del contacto con superficies u objetos contaminados.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Es posible que una persona pueda contraer COVID-19 al tocar una superficie u objeto que tiene el virus y luego tocarse la boca, la nariz o posiblemente los ojos, pero no se cree que esta sea la forma principal en que el virus untado.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>¿Cómo mantenerse seguro?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Como conductor, entra en contacto con muchas personas durante todo el día, lo que aumenta el riesgo de contraer el virus o propagarlo. A continuación se presentan formas de mantenerse seguro y saludable:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Cómo limpiar su auto</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wZ-cyxVUmg8\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wZ-cyxVUmg8\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Desinfecte las partes del automóvil que se tocan con mayor frecuencia: volante, asientos traseros, manijas de pasajeros, cinturones de seguridad, botones del automóvil y reposacabezas.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/2020/03/12/coronavirus-car-interior-cleaning-how-to/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Aquí hay consejos más detallados sobre cómo limpiar su automóvil durante el Coronavirus.</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Cómo lavarse las manos</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-ELZ0bcMfkM\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-ELZ0bcMfkM\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sabemos que es difícil encontrar un baño para lavarse las manos, por lo que recomendamos mantener lo siguiente en su automóvil para que pueda lavarse las manos mientras viaja:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Botella de agua con gorra deportiva</li><li>Jabón</li><li>Toallas de papel para que puedas secarte completamente las manos</li><li>Bolsa de plástico para tirar la toalla de papel</li><li>Recuerde que debe lavarse las manos durante al menos 20 segundos.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bQCP7waTRWU\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Aquí hay un video para mostrarle cómo lavarse las manos adecuadamente, para que no olvide ningún lugar oculto.</a></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>El coronavirus se está extendiendo rápidamente por todo el mundo. La mejor manera de mantenerse a salvo a sí mismo, a su familia y a su comunidad es quedarse en casa si cree que podría enfermarse, incluso si se trata solo del resfriado común. Además, evite el espacio público y manténgase alejado de las personas cuando no esté conduciendo.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://driversbenefits.org/disinfect\">Haga clic aquí para leer sobre más formas de mantenerse a salvo.</a></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>¿Qué debe hacer si se siente enfermo?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Cómo obtener acceso gratuito a un médico las 24 horas del día, los 7 días de la semana con \"Drivers Benefits\"</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gLFONWswfnI\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gLFONWswfnI\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Haga una cita.</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yMEZsownD1s\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yMEZsownD1s\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Si tiene algún síntoma de COVID-19, como fiebre, dificultad para respirar y tos, llame a un médico de inmediato. Como miembro de Drivers Benefits, obtienes acceso gratuito las 24 horas, los 7 días de la semana a MDLIVE *. Usted y su familia inmediata pueden usar la aplicación, o llamar directamente, para chatear con un médico en más de 150 idiomas cuando y donde sea.&nbsp;<strong>CHaga clic aquí para descargar la aplicación MDLIVE en&nbsp;<a href=\"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/mdlive/id839671393\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Apple App Store&nbsp;</a>o&nbsp;<a href=\"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.mdlive.mobile&amp;hl=en_US\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Google Play Store</a>&nbsp;hoy mismo, o simplemente llame al&nbsp;<a href=\"tel:888-574-2864\">1-888-574-2864</a>.&nbsp;</strong><strong>Actualmente, los tiempos de espera de MDLIVE son más largos de lo habitual. Sin embargo, están contratando más médicos, por lo que esto no debería seguir siendo un problema. Puede usar la aplicación para programar una cita para no tener que esperar por teléfono o arriesgarse a acudir a un consultorio abarrotado.&nbsp;</strong>Si aún no es miembro, regístrese hoy aquí o llame al&nbsp;<a href=\"tel:1-833-814-8590\">1-833-814-8590</a>&nbsp;para activar sus beneficios hoy.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Salud y Seguridad','','inherit','closed','closed','','371-revision-v1','','','2020-09-01 18:34:36','2020-09-01 23:34:36','',371,'http://drivers-benefits.local/news/371-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (375,2,'2020-09-01 18:37:31','2020-09-01 23:37:31','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>How Drivers Can Stay Safe During COVID-19</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Drivers Benefits is committed to providing news relevant to drivers about how to protect themselves and what to do if they are sick. We are going to update this page and continue to make it better.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The most recently updated material will be highlighted in blue.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Last updated: 08/19/2020</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>NEW:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://driversbenefits.org/covid-19/#firstsafe\">“What face coverings are the most effective?”</a></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Don’t speak English? Read the pages we made for drivers in <a href=\"https://drivers072120.wpengine.com/covid-19/health-safety?lang=es\">Español</a>, <a href=\"/covid-19/health-safety?lang=zh-hans\">中文</a> and <a href=\"/covid-19/health-safety?lang=fr\">Français</a>.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Disclaimer:&nbsp;</strong>This guide is not meant to constitute legal or professional advice. Please consult a lawyer for any legal advice.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>What is COVID-19?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Copy content to copied here.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>How to stay safe?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Copy content to copied here.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/29GUfvdOVJg\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/29GUfvdOVJg\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Copy content to copied here.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/bK8RLzjcwfg\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/bK8RLzjcwfg\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Copy content to copied here.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Health Webinar with New York City Department of Health</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/iv61DmRvH7Y\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/iv61DmRvH7Y\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Copy content to copied here.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>What Should You Do If You Feel Sick?</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/1-2vy_SoOqo\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/1-2vy_SoOqo\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/wJ9z-IcIIaQ\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/wJ9z-IcIIaQ\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you have any COVID-19 symptoms, like fever, shortness of breath, and cough, call a doctor immediately. As a Drivers Benefits member, you get free, 24/7 access to MDLIVE*. You and your immediate family can use the app, or call directly, to chat with a doctor in more than 150 languages whenever or wherever.&nbsp;<strong>Click here to download the MDLIVE app on the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/mdlive/id839671393\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Apple App Store&nbsp;</a>or the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.mdlive.mobile&amp;hl=en_US\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Google Play Store</a>&nbsp;today, or just call at&nbsp;<a href=\"tel:888-574-2864\">1-888-574-2864</a>.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>You can use the app to schedule an appointment so you don’t need to wait on the phone or risk going to a crowded doctor’s office.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you’re not yet a member, sign up today&nbsp;<a href=\"https://driversbenefits.org/activate-now/?utm_source=WB&amp;utm_medium=lp&amp;utm_campaign=Covid19\">here</a>&nbsp;or call&nbsp;<a href=\"tel:1-833-814-8590\">1-833-814-8590</a>&nbsp;to activate your benefits today.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>*MDLIVE is paid for by The Black Car Fund.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Get Tested</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The New York City Department of Health and Mental Hygiene is recommending anyone who has COVID-19 symptoms should get a test.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are plenty of ways to find a test near you:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>New York City Department of Health testing website is&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www1.nyc.gov/site/coronavirus/get-tested/covid-19-testing.page\">here.</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>New York State Department of Health testing website is&nbsp;<a href=\"https://coronavirus.health.ny.gov/covid-19-testing\">here.</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can get a free walk-in test at the locations listed&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.nychealthandhospitals.org/covid-19-testing-sites/\">here</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you have questions about any symptoms you’re experiencing and don’t have a primary care provider, you can call the 24-hour state hotline at<a href=\"tel: 1-888-364-3065\">1-888-364-3065</a>,&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href=\"tel: 311\">311&nbsp;</a>to receive assistance on making an appointment for a COVID-19 test.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Sign up for Duke Community Health Watch</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You should also consider signing up for Duke Community Health Watch. In this program, they will:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Help you monitor any symptoms you may be having and provide guidance on how to care for yourself at home</li><li>Provide guidance on when to seek medical care if your symptoms increase</li><li>Support you in following recommendations from the Centers for Disease Control and your local public health department</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you are interested in learning more about the program and applying, please click&nbsp;<a href=\"https://covidwatch.dukehealth.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">here</a>&nbsp;for more information.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Additional Resources</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you still have questions about COVID-19 and driving, we recommend you go to the CDC’s guidance on “Rideshare, Taxi, Limo, and other Passenger Drivers-for-Hire”&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/community/organizations/rideshare-drivers-for-hire.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">here</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Health & Safety','','inherit','closed','closed','','36-revision-v1','','','2020-09-01 18:37:31','2020-09-01 23:37:31','',36,'http://drivers-benefits.local/news/36-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (376,2,'2020-09-01 18:41:33','2020-09-01 23:41:33','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>How Drivers Can Stay Safe During COVID-19</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Drivers Benefits is committed to providing news relevant to drivers about how to protect themselves and what to do if they are sick. We are going to update this page and continue to make it better.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The most recently updated material will be highlighted in blue.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Last updated: 08/19/2020</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>NEW:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://driversbenefits.org/covid-19/#firstsafe\">“What face coverings are the most effective?”</a></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Don’t speak English? Read the pages we made for drivers in <a href=\"https://drivers072120.wpengine.com/covid-19/health-safety?lang=es\">Español</a>, <a href=\"/covid-19/health-safety?lang=zh-hans\">中文</a> and <a href=\"/covid-19/health-safety?lang=fr\">Français</a>.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Disclaimer:&nbsp;</strong>This guide is not meant to constitute legal or professional advice. Please consult a lawyer for any legal advice.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>What is COVID-19?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>COVID-19, also known as Coronavirus, is a very contagious and dangerous virus, with symptoms including cough, shortness of breath, fever, loss of taste or smell, sore throat, headache, and muscle pain.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The CDC recently added congestion or runny nose, nausea, and diarrhea as symptoms as well.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Who’s at risk?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Everyone is at risk. But those who are at a higher risk of getting very sick are older adults and those who suffer from heart disease, diabetes, and lung disease.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can learn more about COVID-19 from the CDC&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/index.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">here.</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>How Does it Spread?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>The virus is thought to spread mainly from person-to-person.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Between people who are in close contact with one another (within about 6 feet).</li><li>Through respiratory droplets produced when an infected person coughs or sneezes.</li><li>These droplets can land in the mouths or noses of people who are nearby or possibly be inhaled into the lungs.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Can someone spread the virus without being sick?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>People are thought to be most contagious when they are most symptomatic (the sickest).</li><li>Spreading the disease is also possible before people show symptoms.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Spread from contact with contaminated surfaces or objects</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A person can get COVID-19 by touching a surface or object that has the virus on it and then touching their own mouth, nose, or possibly their eyes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>What if I think I already had COVID-19?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can get an antibody test to find out if this was the case. The implications of a positive antibody test are unclear at this time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can go to any CityMD location to receive an antibody test. Their locations are <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://www.citymd.com/urgent-care-locations\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>. Northwell Health Urgent Care is also providing antibody tests. Their locations are <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://www.gohealthuc.com/nyc/covid-19-antibody-test\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>. Fees may apply.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>How to stay safe?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>s a driver, you come into contact with many people throughout the day, increasing your risk of getting the virus or spreading it. Below are ways to stay safe and healthy:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Wear a Face Covering</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On April 15th, New York Governor Andrew Cuomo issued an executive order requiring members of the public to wear a face covering when social distancing cannot be kept. This would include being inside a car. The order goes into effect on Friday, April 17th.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can find the executive order&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.governor.ny.gov/news/no-20217-continuing-temporary-suspension-and-modification-laws-relating-disaster-emergency\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">here.</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>New York City is distributing face coverings. You can find a list of times and locations&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www1.nyc.gov/site/coronavirus/resources/facecoverings.page\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">here.</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As of April 2nd, the New York City Department of Health and Mental Hygiene released a guidance recommending that all New Yorkers wear a face covering when they are outside of their homes, and, in particular, whenever using car services. We have copied some of the most important guidelines for drivers below. You can find the full guidance&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www1.nyc.gov/assets/doh/downloads/pdf/imm/covid-19-face-covering-faq.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">here</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>UPDATED: What type of face covering is better — paper or cloth?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Either paper or cloth face covering is fine — as long as you are covering your nose and mouth. However, please do not hoard paper masks, especially medical-grade masks, such as N95 masks or surgical masks. These masks are in very short supply and our health care providers need masks to stay healthy and to care for the most critically ill. Health care workers cannot maintain distance from others, avoid sick people, or avoid contact with others’ bodily fluids such as saliva, so it is essential that we reserve masks for them.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Duke University recently did a study that ranked the most effective face coverings. You can check out a summary of the results&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nypost.com/2020/08/11/duke-university-face-mask-researchers-share-more-on-study/\">here</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>How often do I need to wash my face covering?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you are using a cloth face covering, we recommend washing once a day by hand or machine using detergent. The face covering should be fully dry before using. People should have a couple of face coverings so they can rotate for washing.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Are there precautions I should take with my face covering?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>In taking on and off a face covering, you will likely touch your face. As such, please wash your hands for 20 seconds with soap and water or, if not available, use an alcohol-based hand sanitizer every time you take on and off your face covering.</li><li>Do not put a used face covering in places where others can touch them or where germs trapped in your face covering can touch other surfaces, such as counter tops or your kitchen table.</li><li>Used paper masks should be thrown out at the end of the day.</li><li>Do not throw your face covering loose in a bag or backpack. We recommend keeping a plastic back with you to store your face covering if you will be taking it off when outside the house.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Are there unsafe hand sanitizer brands I should be avoiding?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Yes. The CDC has deemed certain hand sanitizers unsafe to use. You can find more information, and a list of products,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.fda.gov/drugs/drug-safety-and-availability/fda-updates-hand-sanitizers-consumers-should-not-use#products\">here</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5><strong>Keep your car clean.</strong></h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/29GUfvdOVJg\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/29GUfvdOVJg\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Disinfect most commonly touched parts of the car: steering wheel, backseats, passenger handles, seatbelts, car buttons, and headrests.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/2020/03/12/coronavirus-car-interior-cleaning-how-to/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Here are more detailed tips</a>&nbsp;for how to clean your car during Coronavirus.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Wash your hands often.</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/bK8RLzjcwfg\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/bK8RLzjcwfg\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We know it’s hard to find a bathroom to wash your hands, so we recommend keeping the following in your car so you can wash your hands on-the-go:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Water bottle with a sports cap</li><li>Soap</li><li>Paper towels so you can fully dry your hands</li><li>Plastic bag to throw out the paper towel</li><li>Remember you must wash your hands for at least 20 seconds.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bQCP7waTRWU\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Here’s a video&nbsp;</a>to show you how to properly wash your hands, so you don’t forget any hidden spots.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Coronavirus is rapidly spreading throughout the world. The best way to keep yourself, your family, and your community safe is to stay home if you think you might be getting sick, even if it’s just the common cold. Also, avoid public space and keep your distance from people when you’re not driving.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Health Webinar with New York City Department of Health</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/iv61DmRvH7Y\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/iv61DmRvH7Y\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In April, we hosted a webinar with the New York City Department of Health’s Rima Oken, Director of Policy, Division of Disease Control and Anna Shats, Community Coordinator for South Brooklyn and Staten Island. We went over how drivers can stay safe and healthy while driving.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can find the videos with Spanish subtitles&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9_YrMtFXujk\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">here</a>, French subtitles&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Lhb7SaF2z2s\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">here</a>, and Chinese subtitles&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3JGSYhTcDjA\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">here</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://driversbenefits.org/disinfect\">Click here to read about more ways to stay safe.</a></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>What Should You Do If You Feel Sick?</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Use telemedicine.</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/1-2vy_SoOqo\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/1-2vy_SoOqo\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Make an appointment.</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/wJ9z-IcIIaQ\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/wJ9z-IcIIaQ\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you have any COVID-19 symptoms, like fever, shortness of breath, and cough, call a doctor immediately. As a Drivers Benefits member, you get free, 24/7 access to MDLIVE*. You and your immediate family can use the app, or call directly, to chat with a doctor in more than 150 languages whenever or wherever.&nbsp;<strong>Click here to download the MDLIVE app on the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/mdlive/id839671393\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Apple App Store&nbsp;</a>or the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.mdlive.mobile&amp;hl=en_US\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Google Play Store</a>&nbsp;today, or just call at&nbsp;<a href=\"tel:888-574-2864\">1-888-574-2864</a>.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>You can use the app to schedule an appointment so you don’t need to wait on the phone or risk going to a crowded doctor’s office.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you’re not yet a member, sign up today&nbsp;<a href=\"https://driversbenefits.org/activate-now/?utm_source=WB&amp;utm_medium=lp&amp;utm_campaign=Covid19\">here</a>&nbsp;or call&nbsp;<a href=\"tel:1-833-814-8590\">1-833-814-8590</a>&nbsp;to activate your benefits today.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>*MDLIVE is paid for by The Black Car Fund.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Get Tested</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The New York City Department of Health and Mental Hygiene is recommending anyone who has COVID-19 symptoms should get a test.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are plenty of ways to find a test near you:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>New York City Department of Health testing website is&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www1.nyc.gov/site/coronavirus/get-tested/covid-19-testing.page\">here.</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>New York State Department of Health testing website is&nbsp;<a href=\"https://coronavirus.health.ny.gov/covid-19-testing\">here.</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can get a free walk-in test at the locations listed&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.nychealthandhospitals.org/covid-19-testing-sites/\">here</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you have questions about any symptoms you’re experiencing and don’t have a primary care provider, you can call the 24-hour state hotline at<a href=\"tel: 1-888-364-3065\">1-888-364-3065</a>,&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href=\"tel: 311\">311&nbsp;</a>to receive assistance on making an appointment for a COVID-19 test.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Sign up for Duke Community Health Watch</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You should also consider signing up for Duke Community Health Watch. In this program, they will:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Help you monitor any symptoms you may be having and provide guidance on how to care for yourself at home</li><li>Provide guidance on when to seek medical care if your symptoms increase</li><li>Support you in following recommendations from the Centers for Disease Control and your local public health department</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you are interested in learning more about the program and applying, please click&nbsp;<a href=\"https://covidwatch.dukehealth.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">here</a>&nbsp;for more information.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Additional Resources</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you still have questions about COVID-19 and driving, we recommend you go to the CDC’s guidance on “Rideshare, Taxi, Limo, and other Passenger Drivers-for-Hire”&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/community/organizations/rideshare-drivers-for-hire.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">here</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Health & Safety','','inherit','closed','closed','','36-revision-v1','','','2020-09-01 18:41:33','2020-09-01 23:41:33','',36,'http://drivers-benefits.local/news/36-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
