INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (457,2,'2020-09-03 13:16:35','2020-09-03 18:16:35','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3><strong>New York State Unemployment Insurance, Pandemic Unemployment Assistance, and Pandemic Unemployment Compensation Guide</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Drivers Benefits wants to make sure drivers understand and apply for the financial assistance programs that are available to them. This page will help you apply for New York State Unemployment Insurance and Pandemic Unemployment Assistance. This page describes what the programs are and how they’re important for drivers, how to apply, and best practices for a smooth process.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The page also includes resources available to drivers who have gone through the process already, and still need additional help securing their benefits.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The most recently updated material will be highlighted in blue.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Last Updated: 07/22</strong><strong>/20</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>The Pandemic Unemployment Compensation ($600 benefit) was not renewed by the federal government.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Don’t speak English? Read the pages we made for drivers in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://translate.google.com/translate?hl=&amp;sl=auto&amp;tl=es&amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fdriversbenefits.org%2Funemployment%2F&amp;sandbox=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Español</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://translate.google.com/translate?hl=&amp;sl=auto&amp;tl=fr&amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fdriversbenefits.org%2Funemployment%2F\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Français</a>, or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://translate.google.com/translate?hl=&amp;sl=auto&amp;tl=zh-TW&amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fdriversbenefits.org%2Funemployment%2F\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">中文</a>.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Disclaimer:</strong>&nbsp;This guide is not meant to constitute legal or professional advice. Please consult a lawyer for any legal advice.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We encourage you to continue to look at this page for updates, as well as checking the New York State Department of Labor&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.labor.ny.gov/home/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">page</a>&nbsp;and the New York State Department of Labor Unemployment Insurance&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.labor.ny.gov/ui/claimantinfo/Claimant%20Handbook%20-%20Languages.shtm\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">claimant handbook</a>. It was last updated in March 2020, and has been translated in 11 languages.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On Saturday, May 16th, the Department of Labor released a useful how-to apply video. We encourage you to watch it&nbsp;<a href=\"https://youtu.be/shXF675SjEc\">here</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Below is a link to our webinar on May 19th with Brooklyn Law School Professor Minna Kotkin, who answered drivers’ questions about Unemployment Insurance and Pandemic Unemployment Assistance. We highly recommend watching the video.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Important update: As of July 22nd, the federal government has not extended the Pandemic Unemployment Compensation benefit, which is the $600 that accompanies the Pandemic Unemployment Assistance. We will update this page with more information about the renewal of the benefit as it becomes available.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tqYqCgrLe64\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tqYqCgrLe64\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 id=\"beforeapplying\"><strong>What to Know Before Applying</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On March 31st, New York State Department of Labor published an updated Frequently Asked Questions regarding Unemployment Benefits.&nbsp; Many of these questions are important to drivers and we have copied those questions and answers for you below. We also added a couple of questions and made some comments on their answers&nbsp;<em>in italics.</em>&nbsp;This section will go over: what these benefits are, how much money you will get, and how long these benefits can last for.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can find the rest of the questions and answers&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.labor.ny.gov/ui/pdfs/ui-covid-faq.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">here</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We also encourage you to read the most up-to-date Frequently Asked Questions sheet released by the New York State Department of Labor about Pandemic Unemployment Assistance, released on April 20th. This can be found <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://labor.ny.gov/ui/pdfs/pua-factsheet.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:atomic-blocks/ab-accordion -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-atomic-blocks-ab-accordion ab-block-accordion\"><details><summary class=\"ab-accordion-title\"><a href=\"https://driversbenefits.org/unemployment/#cf9e2502b2546bf82\">UPDATED: What are these benefits?</a></summary><div class=\"ab-accordion-text\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On March 27, 2020, the President of the United States signed a law that provides additional Unemployment Insurance (“UI”) assistance to workers impacted by COVID-19. This new law provides:&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Pandemic Unemployment Assistance –  This includes Unemployment Assistance for people who usually aren’t eligible, including drivers like you.; </li><li>Pandemic Unemployment Compensation – An additional $600 per week, on top of regular benefits, to all UI <em>and PUA</em> recipients (<em>Drivers Benefits</em> note: This expired on July 26th); and, </li><li>Pandemic Emergency Unemployment Compensation – An additional 13 weeks of UI <em>and PUA</em> benefits, beyond the regular 26 weeks already provided, for a total of 39 weeks of coverage.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></div></details></div>\n<!-- /wp:atomic-blocks/ab-accordion -->','Unemployment Guide','','inherit','closed','closed','','240-revision-v1','','','2020-09-03 13:16:35','2020-09-03 18:16:35','',240,'http://drivers-benefits.local/news/240-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
