\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Pandemic Unemployment Assistance –  This includes Unemployment Assistance for people who usually aren’t eligible, including drivers like you.; </li><li>Pandemic Unemployment Compensation – An additional $600 per week, on top of regular benefits, to all UI <em>and PUA</em> recipients (<em>Drivers Benefits</em> note: This expired on July 26th); and, </li><li>Pandemic Emergency Unemployment Compensation – An additional 13 weeks of UI <em>and PUA</em> benefits, beyond the regular 26 weeks already provided, for a total of 39 weeks of coverage.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></div></details></div>\n<!-- /wp:atomic-blocks/ab-accordion -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Pandemic Unemployment Assistance (“PUA”) – Extended Eligibility for UI Benefits</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:atomic-blocks/ab-accordion -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-atomic-blocks-ab-accordion ab-block-accordion\"><details><summary class=\"ab-accordion-title\">How many things do I have to do before getting money?*</summary><div class=\"ab-accordion-text\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Drivers Benefits Note: There are some steps you will have to do before receiving money from the government. We are here to help you during every step of the way.&nbsp;</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>These are the steps you have to take to receive money (detailed help follows):</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li><em>Create a NY.gov ID</em></li><li>Apply for New York State Unemployment Insurance&nbsp;<em>&amp; Pandemic Unemployment Assistance on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://unemployment.labor.ny.gov/login\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">one form</a></em></li><li>Wait for a call from a representative of New York State Department of Labor</li><li><em>Regardless of receiving a call, you should ALWAYS c</em>ertify your benefits each Sunday&nbsp;</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Under their new application, , you will be automatically directed to the Pandemic Unemployment Assistance application.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Once the New York State Department of Labor approves your claim, you can expect this money in 2-3 weeks.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>If you filled out an older version of the application, DO NOT RE-APPLY. This is one&nbsp;</em><em>of the biggest</em><em>&nbsp;reasons why payments are being delayed. As frustrating and difficult as it is, the Department of Labor wants you to wait until they get in touch with you.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>As we learn more from drivers’ experiences filling out this form and any updates from the New York State Department of Labor, we will update this page.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></details></div>\n<!-- /wp:atomic-blocks/ab-accordion -->','Unemployment Guide','','inherit','closed','closed','','240-revision-v1','','','2020-09-03 14:29:47','2020-09-03 19:29:47','',240,'http://drivers-benefits.local/news/240-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
